
Overview of verb thresh

The verb thresh has 4 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (1) convulse, thresh, thresh about, thrash, thrash about, slash, toss, jactitate -- (move or stir about violently; "The feverish patient thrashed around in his bed")
2. flail, thresh -- (move like a flail; thresh about; "Her arms were flailing")
3. thrash, thresh -- (beat the seeds out of a grain)
4. thrash, thresh, lam, flail -- (give a thrashing to; beat hard)
